text.tspan: Equality of civil liberties across social groups weighted by population,
Based on the expert assessments and index by V-Dem. It captures the extent to which social groups — defined by language,
ethnicity, religion, race, region, and/or caste — are free from forced labor, have property rights and access to the justice system,
and enjoy freedoms of movement. Higher scores mean more equality.
Source: OWID based on V-Dem (v13); Gapminder (v6); HYDE (v3.2); UN (2022)
